rchaeological and historical sources to illuminate the various settings in which we see this late ancient man at work. This vivid historical biography traces Paulinus's intellectual and spiritual journey and at the same time explores many facets of the late ancient Roman world. In addition to filling out the details of Paulinus's life at Nola, Trout looks in depth at Paulinus before his ascetic conversion, providing a new assessment of this formative period to better understand Paulinus's subsequent importance within the influential ascetic and ecclesiastical circles of his age. Trout also highlights Paulinus's place in the swirl of rebellions and heresies of the time, in the pagan revival of the 390s, and especially in the development of a new genre of Christian poetry. And, he examines anew Paulinus's relationships with such figures as Jerome, Rufinus, and Augustine. Trout fully explores the complexity of a figure who has too often been simplified and provides new insights into the kaleidoscopic character of the age in which he lived.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aChristian saintsxBiographyxItalyxNola. 0aChristian saintsxCorrespondencexItalyxNola. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolavBiography. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolavCorrespondence. 0aChristian saintszItalyzNolaxCorrespondence. 0aChristianity and literaturexRome. 0aChristianity and literaturezRome. 0aPoets, LatinxBiographyxItalyxNola. 0aPoets, LatinxCorrespondencexItalyxNola. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolavBiography. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolavCorrespondence. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolaxBiography. 0aPoets, LatinzItalyzNolaxCorrespondence. 4aAncient Archaeology. 4aAncient History. 4aChristianity. 4aNear and Middle Eastern History. 4aOvid. 4aclassical lit